I am writing the review for Dell mouse model no. MS116, after using this for almost 3 years. I bought this on 2nd May 2019, and this review has been written on 17th April 2021. I chose to write it's review because it is finally at the end of its life, atleast its left click is. Although it is still functional, its left click started 'double clicking' last week. I mention its pros and cons below:Pros:1) This mouse lasted for a long time. Three years is a very good lifetime for a general purpose Mouse.2) I purchased it at a fairly low price. And even today it is available at a low cost.3) I have used it frequently, and for all kinds of work, whether editing 'MS word', googling,  image editing, gaming. It works wonderfully. It never failed. I have played all kinds of games with it. Although not meant for professional gaming. I can safely say that it should work with almost all games.4) It is comfortable to hold, though people with very small hand may find it difficult to reach the ends of the buttons. It can be used by almost everyone. It does not have any sharp edges or corners.5) Works on most surfaces.6) Length of wire attached is ample. It is about 1.5 meters.7) Outer material is made of good quality plastic with Matte finish.8) It stays mostly clean, however if your hands sweat frequently,  then you may want to clean it once in a while,  otherwise dirt and grit from your hand can accumulate in it over time.Cons:1) The size of my hand is that of an average Indian man. So, I find it comfortable to use. But people with small hands may find the backside to be somewhat larger, especially if you are in the habit of resting your wrist on the table behind the mouse. In that particular case, you may find that you are not entirely able to reach the end of the buttons,  though they would still be clickable. This can make some people uncomfortable initially but with use one can adapt to it.2) Unlike gaming mouse it does not have extra buttons,  to adjust dpi or Mouse speed.Overall, it is simple, beautiful and economical mouse. I will buy it again.

Brought this mouse back in 2022, the build quality feels sturdy and not flimsy unlike many cheap mice. Sensor works fine i casually played valorant and minecraft and didn't face any issues. People are able to double click and drag click on this mouse but i was never able to do so. Overall a great product at a great price from a reputed brand.

reviewDescription: I'm writing this review after TWO YEARS of usage, and I got this in an discounted sale, for around 180 bucks that time :) A medium sized mouse that's good for large hands like mine! if u really want a mouse and you're under a TIGHT BUDGET, just go for this one, its an amazing and really LONG LASTING. Clean look, LIGHTWEIGHT, but yet plasticky, and click sounds are quite loud, scroll bar isnt so smooth, but under this budget, couldn't expect more and it really does the job, and I almost got used to all of the above mentioned cons eventually, and extremely surprised by its LONGEVITY, cuz generally mouses of this price didn't last long for me, not even a year, they stop working. But this isn't one of them. Pro tip, UNLESS AND UNTIL YOU HANDLE IT REALLY GOOD, AND HAVE THE PRACTICE OF KEEPIN IT PACKED OR BOXED IN A SAFE PLACE WHEN NOT IN USE, ANY MOUSE WOULD MALFUNCTION SOONER, just treat this mouse like any other mouse you'll get for thousands of bucks, it will last longer :) Great for PROFESSIONAL USE, video and photo editing, etc. Not so great for gaming, for playing games like Rainbow Six Seige, Valorant etc., due to less precision and response time(tested it, still you can manage to do well upto an extent, depends on how good of a gamer you are to understand and get used to the latency and response time of your mouse over time), but still you can obviously play some good old offline story mode games like GTA V. I'm a designer and I use it mostly for rendering, and modeling stuff, surprisingly this mouse seemed to do a great job for the price. Back then when I bought this, there were barely 100 reviews, and now I'm actually surprised to see these many reviews on this product. Overall, this is a really good budget mouse, and really really long lasting, as far as my experience at least.
